8. Decides to review measures at the end of a specified period, considering progress in Côte d’Ivoire’s peace and national reconciliation process;

9. Requests the Secretary-General to re-establish a Group of Experts for 6 months to monitor and report on arms, diamonds, and related issues;

10. Requests UNOCI to communicate information gathered on arms and diamond supplies;

11. Requests the French Government to communicate similar information gathered by French forces;

12. Requests the Kimberley Process to communicate information on diamond production and illicit export;

13. Urges cooperation with the Committee, Group of Experts, UNOCI, and French forces;

14. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
